SIMPLE: muddiness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Muddiness
<hw>Mud"di*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The condition or
quality of being muddy; turbidness; foulness caused by mud, dirt, or
sediment; <as>as, the <ex>muddiness</ex> of a stream</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Obscurity or confusion, as in treatment of a
subject; intellectual dullness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muddle</ent>⟦br⟧
